President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Hester Maria Peirce as Commissioner of the Securities and Exchange Commission. Peirce is currently a Senior Research Fellow and Director of the Financial Markets Working Group at the Mercatus Center at George Mason University. She has previously served as Senior Counsel for the Minority Staff of the Senate Committee on Banking, Housing, and Urban Affairs, as well as in various roles at the Securities and Exchange Commission. Peirce holds a B.A. from Case Western Reserve University and a J.D. from Yale Law School.